{
  "stem": "27335.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, he escaped with some other people, and his closest friend was the- the village-- the primash-- the gypsy primash-- [LAUGHS] violenced prima-- and they-- they escaped into Austria.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and that's where-- because my father came from there, he knew his way around.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then-- and they were able to get a- get a job, and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the Terror-- the [NON-ENGLISH], who was-- well, this was called the White Terror, the [NON-ENGLISH] is White Terror, supplied the revolution.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was so severe, and so brutal-- and anti-Semite, mind you [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That the international community-- through the League of Nations, it was functioning already-- declared an amnesty, and they forced [INAUDIBLE] to declare amnesty to the-- to the-- to the refugees, and so on.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was in 1921, when father-- my father came back from Austria, and rejoined the family, again.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That I remember-- I remember-- very-- very vividly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then-- then he was a marked man, you see.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The [INAUDIBLE] army-- that, uh, brutal force, suppressive force-- [INAUDIBLE] brutal and-- around the globe-- the Hungarian [INAUDIBLE] army.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, he visited and-- and he-- and he aggravated my father.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were always on his-- they shadowed him all the time, you see.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was a life on the [INAUDIBLE], already, [INAUDIBLE] And in the first-- first years, I remember, in school, you are-- you are fingered by- by your schoolmates, that all-- that all these communists and Bolsheviks, and then the [INAUDIBLE] or Reds, and so on.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was because, uh, one of these teacher who came as a refugee from Transylvania, escaping the Romanians, became, uh, one of my teachers in Protestant school, school you see.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, well, he knew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He hated my father.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And not only my father, but the-- the-- the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
